body.answer:
Albert Einstein died on April 18, 1955, at the age of 76.

He passed away at Princeton Hospital in New Jersey, USA, due to an abdominal aortic aneurysm. Einstein had refused surgery, saying: "I want to go when I want. It is tasteless to prolong life artificially. I have done my share, it is time to go. I will do it elegantly."

Einstein's death was a significant event in the scientific community and around the world, marking the loss of one of the most brilliant and influential physicists in history. His contributions to science, particularly his theory of relativity, continue to be foundational in modern physics.
